                  <handDesc>
                     <!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine and regular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black; red (strong red).</seg>
                        Scribe: Takla Hāymānot. Takla
                        Hymannot is mentioned as the scribe on <locus target="#16rb">16rb</locus>,
                        54rb.&#xD; &#xD; Possibly the same scribe as in Mss. QDS-003,
                           MAKM-060.<date>Late 19th - early 20th cent.</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr> ብ፡</abbr> for <expan>ብሂል፡</expan> (<locus from="10rb" to="11ra"/>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሀበ፡ እግ፡ በኃ፡ ዝ(ን)፡ አስ፡ ሃይ፡ ርት፡</abbr> for <expan>ሀበነ፡ እግዚኦ፡ በኃይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ ሃይማኖተ፡ ርትዕተ፡ </expan> 
                              (<locus from="18vb" to="23vb"/>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>– አድ፡ እግ፡ አም፡ በኃ፡ ዝ(ን)፡ አስ፡</abbr> for <expan>አድኀነነ፡ እግዚኦ፡
                                 አምላክነ፡ በኃይለ፡ ዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ </expan> (<locus from="37va" to="40ra"/>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>እግዚኦ፡ አሜ፡</abbr> for <expan>እግዚአብሔር፡ አሜን፡ </expan> (<locus from="43ra" to="44ra"/>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ለዓለ፡ ዓለ፡ አ፡</abbr> for <expan>ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን </expan> (<locus target="#54rb"/>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ሰ(ላ)፡</abbr> for <expan>ሰላም፡ </expan> (<locus from="54vb" to="57va"/>)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>(ገብ)፡ መን(ፈ)፡ ቅ(ዱ)፡</abbr> for <expan>ገብረ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ </expan>
                                 (<locus from="54vb" to="57va"/>)</item>
                        </list>
                        
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the name of the owners; the word
                           salām; several lines on the incipit page of Text I (fol. 4r); the incipit
                           of the daily readings; the word bǝrsabaḥel on fol. 48va; elements of the
                           punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">The scribe Takla Hāymānot has a
                        peculiar way of shaping the loop of the letter
                        ግ.<!--The names of this hands need to be replaced by appropriate refs.--></handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#3r"/>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Donation note which states that Gabra Ḥǝywat donated the manuscript to the monastery
                              of <placeName ref="INS0174MAKM">May ʾAnbasā</placeName>.</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ዝመጽሓፍ፡ ዘአባ፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡ ዘወሀባ፡ ለታቦተ፡ ኪዳነ፡ ምሕረት፡ ማየ፡ አንበሳ፡ ድብር፡ ገነት፡</q>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus from="58vb" to="59r"/>
                           <desc type="DonationNote">Donation note which states that Gabra Ḥǝywat bought the manuscript with his money
                              and donated it to the monastery of <placeName ref="INS0174MAKM">May ʾAnbasā</placeName> in the year 1930/31
                              A.D. (the date is misspelled, but can be reconstructed to the year of
                              mercy 1923 = 1930/31 A.D.).</desc>
                           <q xml:lang="gez">ዝመጽሓፍ፡ ዘአባ፡ ገብረ፡ ሕይወት፡ ዘአጥረዩ፡ በንዋዩ፡ ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፨ በ፲፻፳፫ዓመተ፡ ምሕረት፨ ወወሀባ፡ ለኪዳነ፡ ምሕረት፡ ማየ፡
                              አንበሳ፡ ከመ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሃ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት፨</q>
                        </item>
                        
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title ʾardǝʾt has been written in blue paint on the
                           front board.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2"><!--2019-04-02+02:00 Updated MAKM-025 
            from DomLib -->
                           <desc type="findingAid">Daily readings of Text I are indicated by the days
                              of the week written in the upper margin, in the main hand: ዘሠሉስ:
                                 <locus target="#11v">fol. 11v</locus> ዘረቡዕ: <locus target="#16r">fol. 16r</locus> ዘሐሙስ: <locus target="#24r">fol. 24r</locus> ዘዓርብ:
                                 <locus target="#34v">fol. 34v</locus> ዘቀዳም: <locus target="#44r">fol. 44r</locus> ዘእኁድ: <locus target="#51v">fol.
                              51v</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
